                  "code": "67781-5",
                  "display": "Summarization of encounter note"
                }
              ]
            },
            "title": "Synthesis"
          },
          {
            "text": {
              "status": "generated",
              "div": "<div xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\">Dear colleague, I am writing to inform you about the hospital course of your patient, an 81-year-old male, admitted on 22/06/2021 due to severe aortic valve stenosis. Upon admission, echocardiography confirmed critical aortic stenosis with significantly reduced valve area and elevated mean pressure gradient. Cardiac catheterization was performed to assess coronary artery status prior to intervention. Following multidisciplinary heart team discussion, given the patient's age and surgical risk profile, the decision was made to proceed with transcatheter aortic valve replacement (TAVR), which was performed successfully on 23/06/2021 without periprocedural complications. Post-procedural echocardiography demonstrated excellent prosthetic valve function with normalised gradients. The patient recovered well and was discharged in stable condition. Please continue antiplatelet therapy and arrange follow-up echocardiography in three months. Do not hesitate to contact me should you require further information.</div>"
            },
            "code": {
              "coding": [
